                <note rend="inline" type="source">033.1140/119: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Chargé in France</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Bliss</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1919-01-07T17:00:00-05:00"
                            >January 7, 1919—5 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>6881. For Davis from Rathbone. Treasury 687. Mission’s 154, January 4, 6 p.m.
                    Yours unnumbered to Secretary. All applications for loans concerning relief
                    should receive your consideration and study. You are expected to discuss the
                    same and to make recommendations to the Treasury.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Polk</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
